---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": "Pool Maintenance Approach",
  "provider": {
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "name": "Perfect Pools",
    "telephone": "(912) 459-0160"
  },
  "areaServed": "Richmond Hill, Savannah, and Coastal Georgia",
  "description": "Our systematic approach to pool care: water chemistry as a system, preventive equipment monitoring, and total transparency with digital service reports."
};

const icons = {
  testTube: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><path d="M14.5 2v17.5c0 1.4-1.1 2.5-2.5 2.5s-2.5-1.1-2.5-2.5V2"/><path d="M8.5 2h7"/><path d="M14.5 16h-5"/></svg>',
  alertCircle: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>',
  eye: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><path d="M2.062 12.348a1 1 0 0 1 0-.696 10.75 10.75 0 0 1 19.876 0 1 1 0 0 1 0 .696 10.75 10.75 0 0 1-19.876 0"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/></svg>',
  checkCircle: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg>',
  droplets: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><path d="M7 16.3c2.2 0 4-1.83 4-4.05 0-1.16-.57-2.26-1.71-3.19S7.29 6.75 7 5.3c-.29 1.45-1.14 2.84-2.29 3.76S3 11.1 3 12.25c0 2.22 1.8 4.05 4 4.05z"/><path d="M12.56 6.6A10.97 10.97 0 0 0 14 3.02c.5 2.5 2 4.9 4 6.5s3 3.5 3 5.5a6.98 6.98 0 0 1-11.91 4.97"/></svg>',
  waves: '<svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="icon"><path d="M2 6c.6.5 1.2 1 2.5 1C7 7 7 5 9.5 5c2.6 0 2.4 2 5 2 2.5 0 2.5-2 5-2 1.3 0 1.9.5 2.5 1"/><path d="M2 12c.6.5 1.2 1 2.5 1 2.5 0 2.5-2 5-2 2.6 0 2.4 2 5 2 2.5 0 2.5-2 5-2 1.3 0 1.9.5 2.5 1"/><path d="M2 18c.6.5 1.2 1 2.5 1 2.5 0 2.5-2 5-2 2.6 0 2.4 2 5 2 2.5 0 2.5-2 5-2 1.3 0 1.9.5 2.5 1"/></svg>',
};

const quoteFormUrl = "https://forms.jeffspoolspa.com/jeffspoolspaservice1/form/MaintenanceLeads/formperma/sZ_cHMy_F4pf-JTi8aCRtmGr78z4LJNGBj_w8_dtEIc";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Our Approach to Pool Care | Science, Consistency & Transparency | Perfect Pools"
  description="How Perfect Pools maintains your pool: water chemistry as a system, preventive equipment monitoring, and total transparency with digital reports. Serving Richmond Hill, Savannah & Coastal Georgia."
  canonicalPath="/our-approach"
  schema={schema}
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Our Approach to Pool Care</h1>
      <p>Why clear water isn't luck — it's science, consistency, and accountability.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Most pool companies treat maintenance like a checklist: dump chlorine, skim the surface,
          and move to the next house. That approach might keep your water from turning completely
          green, but it doesn't create truly balanced, healthy pool chemistry — and it doesn't catch
          equipment problems before they become expensive emergencies.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do things differently. Here's exactly how we maintain your pool — and why it matters.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The Three Pillars -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Three pillars of Perfect Pool care</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__icon">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.testTube} />
          </div>
          <h3>Water Chemistry as a System</h3>
          <p>
            Your pool water isn't just "chlorinated" or "not chlorinated." It's a delicate
            balance of pH, alkalinity, calcium hardness, stabilizer, and sanitizer.
          </p>
          <p>
            When one of these is off, it affects everything else. Too much calcium makes
            chlorine less effective. Low alkalinity causes pH swings. We test and adjust all
            of these factors together — not just throw in chlorine and hope for the best.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__icon">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.alertCircle} />
          </div>
          <h3>Preventive Equipment Monitoring</h3>
          <p>
            Every visit includes a full inspection: pump pressure, filter condition, water
            flow rate, skimmer baskets, and equipment sounds.
          </p>
          <p>
            A pump that starts making a different noise isn't "fine." It's a warning sign
            that a bearing is wearing out. We catch these early — before a $200 repair becomes
            a $1,500 emergency replacement in July.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-card__icon">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.eye} />
          </div>
          <h3>Total Transparency</h3>
          <p>
            After every visit, you get a digital service report with chemical readings, what
            we adjusted, and photos if we notice anything.
          </p>
          <p>
            You should never wonder, "Did they actually come this week?" or "Why is my bill
            higher this month?" If we add something beyond standard chemicals, you know about
            it before it happens.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What a Typical Visit Looks Like -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align:left;margin-inline:0;">
        <h2>What a typical service visit looks like</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="visit-steps">
        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.checkCircle} />
            <div>
              <h3>Arrival & Visual Inspection (2-3 min)</h3>
              <p>We check the pool surface for debris, algae spots, staining, and water level. We also look at the deck area for safety issues or equipment leaks.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.testTube} />
            <div>
              <h3>Water Testing (3-5 min)</h3>
              <p>We test for free chlorine, pH, total alkalinity, calcium hardness, and stabilizer (CYA). These readings are logged in your service report.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.droplets} />
            <div>
              <h3>Chemical Adjustment (5-7 min)</h3>
              <p>Based on test results, we adjust pH, alkalinity, and add chlorine or salt as needed. We also add algaecide or clarifier if the water needs it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.waves} />
            <div>
              <h3>Surface Cleaning & Basket Service (5-7 min)</h3>
              <p>We skim leaves and debris from the surface, empty skimmer and pump baskets, and brush the pool walls and steps as needed.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.alertCircle} />
            <div>
              <h3>Equipment Check (3-5 min)</h3>
              <p>We inspect pump operation, filter pressure gauge, heater (if applicable), salt cell condition, and automation settings. Any abnormalities are noted.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-card">
          <div class="visit-card__inner">
            <Fragment set:html={icons.eye} />
            <div>
              <h3>Documentation & Report (2-3 min)</h3>
              <p>Before we leave, we log all readings and actions in our system. You'll receive a digital report with photos if we spotted anything unusual.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-italic" style="color:var(--color-text-light);margin-top:2rem;">
        Total visit time: 20-30 minutes, depending on pool size and condition
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Water Chemistry Explained -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="section-header" style="text-align:left;margin-inline:0;">
        <h2>Pool chemistry in plain English</h2>
        <p style="text-align:left;">You don't need to be a chemist to understand your pool. Here's what the numbers mean:</p>
      </div>

      <div class="chemistry-stack">
        <div class="chemistry-card">
          <h3>Free Chlorine (1-3 ppm)</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-light);line-height:1.7;">
            This is your sanitizer. It kills bacteria, algae, and other contaminants. Too low
            and you get algae. Too high and it irritates eyes and skin. We keep it in the
            sweet spot.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chemistry-card">
          <h3>pH (7.2-7.6)</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-light);line-height:1.7;">
            pH measures how acidic or basic your water is. Low pH (acidic) corrodes equipment
            and irritates skin. High pH makes chlorine ineffective and causes cloudy water.
            This is one of the most important numbers.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chemistry-card">
          <h3>Total Alkalinity (80-120 ppm)</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-light);line-height:1.7;">
            Think of this as pH's "shock absorber." Proper alkalinity prevents pH from swinging
            wildly every time you add chemicals or it rains. Low alkalinity = unstable water.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chemistry-card">
          <h3>Calcium Hardness (200-400 ppm)</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-light);line-height:1.7;">
            Too low and your water "hungers" for calcium, pulling it from your pool surface
            and equipment (causing damage). Too high and you get scaling on tiles and fixtures.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chemistry-card">
          <h3>Stabilizer / CYA (30-50 ppm)</h3>
          <p style="color:var(--color-text-light);line-height:1.7;">
            This protects chlorine from UV breakdown in the sun. Without it, chlorine
            evaporates in hours. Too much and chlorine becomes ineffective (common problem
            with tab feeders and salt pools).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to experience the difference?</h2>
      <p>Join hundreds of coastal Georgia homeowners who trust us with their pools.</p>
      <div class="cta-section__buttons">
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}plans`} class="btn btn--cta btn--lg">View Service Plans</a>
        <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}reviews`} class="btn btn--outline-white btn--lg">Read Customer Reviews</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
